Saudi Arabia hopes to increase the volumeof its oil exports to Japan through expanding bilateral trade,Saudi Arabian Interior Minister Naif bin Abdul-Aziz said.    He told a Tokyo reception his country hopes to raise crudeand products exports to Japan to earlier levels, but did notelaborate. To promote trade, Saudi Arabia is inviting Japaneseindustries to do business there, he said.    Japanese firms now have long-term contracts to import atotal of 150,000 barrels per day of Saudi crude. REUTER&#3;